    <fr:title text="Karatsuba multiplication by Löb induction">Karatsuba multiplication by Löb induction</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Multiply <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> using three half-size multiplications
instead of four. Split both numbers at a half-width base <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x = x_0 + B \cdot  x_1,
   \qquad 
   y = y_0 + B \cdot  y_1.]]></fr:tex>
Over pairs of numbers measured by a bound on their digit count, the
functor of subproblems requests the three products
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[X{\mathopen {}\left (x_0, y_0\right )\mathclose {}},
   \qquad 
   X{\mathopen {}\left (x_1, y_1\right )\mathclose {}},
   \qquad 
   X{\mathopen {}\left (x_1 + x_0,\; y_1 + y_0\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
each at a strictly smaller digit bound —
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" title="Locally contractive endofunctors" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FQ/" type="local">locally contractive</fr:link> by that certificate.</html:p>
    <html:p>The coalgebra performs the split. The motive at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (x, y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sum _{p} {\mathopen {}\left (p = x \cdot  y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> — a number with a proof that it is
the product — so the recursive results arrive as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[z_0 = x_0 y_0,
   \qquad 
   z_2 = x_1 y_1,
   \qquad 
   z_{11} = {\mathopen {}\left (x_1 + x_0\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (y_1 + y_0\right )\mathclose {}},]]></fr:tex>
each with its proof, and the algebra recombines them through
Karatsuba's identity
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[x \cdot  y
   = z_2 \cdot  B^2 + {\mathopen {}\left (z_{11} - z_2 - z_0\right )\mathclose {}} \cdot  B + z_0,]]></fr:tex>
its one proof obligation.</html:p>
    <html:p>The <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" title="Local contractivity makes every coalgebra recursive" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FW/" type="local">hylomorphism</fr:link> of this coalgebra and algebra is the
multiplier: it evaluates on numerals, correct by the type of its
result.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
